# 2bc02091e6fb4e07a8784051a40c75b3
#: ../../admin-guide/files/storage.config.en.rst:24
msgid ""
"The :file:`storage.config` file (by default, located in "
"``/usr/local/etc/trafficserver/``) lists all the files, directories, "
"and/or hard disk partitions that make up the Traffic Server cache. After "
"you modify the :file:`storage.config` file the new settings will not be "
"effective until Traffic Server is restarted."
msgstr ""

# d65c5b63e8ad458bbb4a5b334ace9365
#: ../../admin-guide/files/storage.config.en.rst:30
msgid "Format"
msgstr ""

# 3bd147792dc14f2f884a1333561ab403
#: ../../admin-guide/files/storage.config.en.rst:32
msgid ""
"The format of the :file:`storage.config` file is a series of lines of the"
" form"
msgstr ""

# b7bec3933cbb4f1ca28bf76615799c42
#: ../../admin-guide/files/storage.config.en.rst:34
msgid "*pathname* *size* [ ``volume=``\\ *number* ] [ ``id=``\\ *string* ]"
msgstr ""

# 4eb963edecf241d28c757c7064648d09
#: ../../admin-guide/files/storage.config.en.rst:36
msgid ""
"where :arg:`pathname` is the name of a partition, directory or file, "
":arg:`size` is the size of the named partition, directory or file (in "
"bytes), and :arg:`volume` is the volume number used in the files "
":file:`volume.config` and :file:`hosting.config`. :arg:`id` is used for "
"seeding the :ref:`assignment-table`. You must specify a size for "
"directories; size is optional for files and raw partitions. :arg:`volume`"
" and arg:`seed` are optional."
msgstr ""

# 84847a48eec048b290b4e80752da205f
#: ../../admin-guide/files/storage.config.en.rst:44
msgid ""
"The :arg:`volume` option is independent of the :arg:`seed` option and "
"either can be used with or without the other, and their ordering on the "
"line is irrelevant."
msgstr ""

# 30bc9c7bfa214224a749a2b2e6d1138b
#: ../../admin-guide/files/storage.config.en.rst:49
msgid ""
"If the :arg:`id` option is used every use must have a unique value for "
":arg:`string`."
msgstr ""

# 3a96f6ab0092497d956d8142087b0138
#: ../../admin-guide/files/storage.config.en.rst:51
msgid "You can use any partition of any size. For best performance:"
msgstr ""

# 705bfdfb1f3c456dad4ab25cc8bf4cbf
#: ../../admin-guide/files/storage.config.en.rst:53
msgid "Use raw disk partitions."
msgstr ""

# ab862a3055d940d585472f997e0e5c90
#: ../../admin-guide/files/storage.config.en.rst:54
msgid "For each disk, make all partitions the same size."
msgstr ""

# 21ff9baa11814caa8782e0b92f2eff99
#: ../../admin-guide/files/storage.config.en.rst:55
msgid "For each node, use the same number of partitions on all disks."
msgstr ""

# 3cb2ea4369df45e58334de5b2b30f784
#: ../../admin-guide/files/storage.config.en.rst:56
msgid ""
"Group similar kinds of storage into different volumes. For example split "
"out SSD's or RAM drives into their own volume."
msgstr ""

# d0a21b4fc1634fb2aad46397019e4793
#: ../../admin-guide/files/storage.config.en.rst:59
msgid ""
"Specify pathnames according to your operating system requirements. See "
"the following examples. In the :file:`storage.config` file, a formatted "
"or raw disk must be at least 128 MB."
msgstr ""

# fa5578827c7d42a281bd3bff3bc59823
#: ../../admin-guide/files/storage.config.en.rst:63
msgid ""
"When using raw disk or partitions, you should make sure the "
":ts:cv:`Traffic Server user <proxy.config.admin.user_id>` used by the "
"Traffic Server process has read and write privileges on the raw disk "
"device or partition. One good practice is to make sure the device file is"
" set with 'g+rw' and the Traffic Server user is in the group which owns "
"the device file.  However, some operating systems have stronger "
"requirements - see the following examples for more information."
msgstr ""

